.TH yes 1
.SH NAME
\*Lyes\*O \- Affirms repetitively
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.PP 
.sS
\*Lyes\*O
\*O[\*Vexpletive\*O]
.sE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "yes command"
.PP 
The \*Lyes\*O command repeatedly outputs \*Ly\*O, or the locale's
equivalent of a \*Ly\*O, or, if specified,
\*Vexpletive\*O.  (The \*LLC_MESSAGES\*O variable
determines the locale's equivalent
of \*Ly\*O or \*Ln\*O (for yes/no queries)).
.PP 
\*Lyes\*O is useful for providing continuous input to a program.
Terminate output by pressing the Interrupt key sequence.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP 
To delete all files in a directory (using the \*Lrm\*O command)
and automatically send an affirmative response
to the request for confirmation, enter:
.iS
yes | rm -i *
\*O\c
.iE
.EQ
delim off
.EN
